# Hexagonal Architecture (Ports & Adapters) — Scout

## Dependency flow (CRITICAL)

Infrastructure → Application → Domain

NEVER reverse this flow. Domain has zero framework imports — no FastAPI,
no Pydantic, no SQLAlchemy. Pure Python with type hints.

## Module structure
````
src/scout/
├── domain/
│   ├── models/         # dataclasses (frozen=True), pure Python
│   ├── exceptions/     # domain errors
│   ├── events/         # domain events (optional, dataclasses)
│   └── ports/          # Protocols (repository and service interfaces)
├── application/
│   ├── services/       # one service per use case (AnalyzeMetricService...)
│   └── dtos/           # plain dataclasses for service input/output
└── infrastructure/
├── api/
│   ├── routers/    # FastAPI APIRouter, one file per resource
│   ├── schemas/    # Pydantic v2 request/response models
│   └── deps.py     # Depends() factories
├── persistence/
│   ├── models/     # SQLAlchemy declarative models
│   ├── repositories/  # SqlalchemyXRepository implementations
│   └── session.py  # AsyncSession factory
├── llm/            # Anthropic Claude adapter
├── prometheus/     # Prometheus HTTP API client
└── config/         # Pydantic Settings
tests/
├── unit/               # pytest -m unit (domain, application)
├── integration/        # pytest -m integration (persistence, external clients)
└── e2e/                # pytest -m e2e (full API flows)
````
## Layer rules

### Domain
- Pure Python, fully typed (`from __future__ import annotations`)
- Models are `@dataclass(frozen=True, slots=True)` when immutable
- Mutable aggregates use `@dataclass` without `frozen` but expose only methods
  (no direct attribute mutation from outside)
- NO imports from FastAPI, Pydantic, SQLAlchemy, anthropic, httpx, etc.
- Ports are `typing.Protocol` classes with `@runtime_checkable` if checked at runtime
- Domain exceptions inherit from a base `DomainError`; use class-level static
  factory methods for common cases:
```python
  class MetricNotFoundError(DomainError):
      @classmethod
      def with_id(cls, metric_id: str) -> "MetricNotFoundError":
          return cls(f"Metric {metric_id} not found")
```

### Application
- One service per use case, named `{Verb}{Noun}Service` (e.g. `AnalyzeMetricService`)
- Services are classes with `__init__` that takes ports (repos, clients) as deps
- Public method is `async def execute(input: XInput) -> XOutput`
- DTOs (`XInput`, `XOutput`) are `@dataclass` in `application/dtos/`
- NO business logic — orchestration and policy only
- NO direct DB calls — only via injected repositories

### Infrastructure
- Routers: one `APIRouter` per resource, mounted under `/api/v1/`
- Pydantic schemas live ONLY in `infrastructure/api/schemas/`. Never in domain.
- Routers are thin: parse Pydantic request → call service → serialize Pydantic response
- SQLAlchemy declarative models in `infrastructure/persistence/models/`
- Repositories implement Domain Protocols and depend on `AsyncSession`
- Repositories return Domain objects, NEVER SQLAlchemy models
- External clients (Claude, Prometheus) implement Domain ports too

## Service contract

Every use case follows this shape:

```python
# application/services/analyze_metric_service.py
class AnalyzeMetricService:
    def __init__(
        self,
        metrics_repo: MetricsRepository,    # Domain Protocol
        llm_client: LlmClient,              # Domain Protocol
    ) -> None:
        self._metrics_repo = metrics_repo
        self._llm_client = llm_client

    async def execute(self, input: AnalyzeMetricInput) -> AnalyzeMetricOutput:
        ...
```

Service input/output dataclasses live in `application/dtos/`.

| Operation | Returns |
|-----------|---------|
| Create | DTO with the new entity's id |
| Update / Delete | DTO with status only, or `None` |
| Read (single) | DTO mirroring the domain object |
| Read (list) | DTO with `items: list[...]` and pagination metadata |

## Domain events (optional)

If a use case emits domain events:
- Define event as `@dataclass(frozen=True)` in `domain/events/`
- Pattern: `{Noun}{PastVerb}Event` (e.g. `AnomalyDetectedEvent`)
- Event publishing via a `DomainEventPublisher` Protocol; default in-memory impl
  for v1, replaceable later

## Naming conventions

| Component | Pattern | Example |
|-----------|---------|---------|
| Service (use case) | `{Verb}{Noun}Service` | `AnalyzeMetricService` |
| Service input DTO | `{Verb}{Noun}Input` | `AnalyzeMetricInput` |
| Service output DTO | `{Verb}{Noun}Output` | `AnalyzeMetricOutput` |
| Domain model | Singular noun | `Metric`, `Anomaly` |
| Domain exception | `{Concept}Error` | `MetricNotFoundError` |
| Domain event | `{Noun}{PastVerb}Event` | `AnomalyDetectedEvent` |
| Repository port | `{Entity}Repository` (Protocol) | `MetricsRepository` |
| Repository impl | `Sqlalchemy{Entity}Repository` | `SqlalchemyMetricsRepository` |
| External client port | `{Service}Client` (Protocol) | `LlmClient`, `PrometheusClient` |
| FastAPI router file | `{resource}.py` | `metrics.py`, `anomalies.py` |
| Request schema | `{Verb}{Noun}Request` | `AnalyzeMetricRequest` |
| Response schema | `{Noun}Response` | `MetricResponse`, `AnomalyResponse` |

## Code style

- `from __future__ import annotations` at top of every file
- Type hints on every function signature, including `-> None`
- mypy strict — no implicit `Any`
- ruff format and ruff check must be clean
- No `print()` — use `structlog` logger
- No commented-out code in commits
- No `TODO` without an issue reference
- Tests, code, comments, docstrings: all in English

## Testing strategy

| Layer | Test type | Marker | Location |
|-------|-----------|--------|----------|
| Domain | pure unit, no I/O | `@pytest.mark.unit` | `tests/unit/domain/` |
| Application | unit with mocks for ports | `@pytest.mark.unit` | `tests/unit/application/` |
| Infrastructure (persistence) | integration with real PostgreSQL | `@pytest.mark.integration` | `tests/integration/persistence/` |
| Infrastructure (api) | e2e via httpx.AsyncClient | `@pytest.mark.e2e` | `tests/e2e/api/` |

Test layout mirrors `src/`. Test files named `test_{module}.py`.

## Architecture checklist (apply during implementation)

**Domain**
- [ ] No imports from `fastapi`, `pydantic`, `sqlalchemy`, or any framework
- [ ] Models use `@dataclass`; immutable ones use `frozen=True`
- [ ] Ports are `typing.Protocol`
- [ ] Exceptions inherit from `DomainError` and use named factory methods

**Application**
- [ ] Service classes with constructor-injected ports
- [ ] Public method is `async def execute(input) -> output`
- [ ] DTOs live in `application/dtos/`, not co-located with services
- [ ] No SQLAlchemy or HTTP client imports

**Infrastructure**
- [ ] Pydantic schemas only in `infrastructure/api/schemas/`
- [ ] Routers thin: schema → service → schema
- [ ] Repositories return Domain objects, never SQLAlchemy models
- [ ] Repositories take `AsyncSession` via constructor or method param
- [ ] All I/O is `async`